      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(image-generation): replace unbounded response.json() with readProviderJsonResponse",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n`src/image-generation/openai-compatible-image-provider.ts:272` calls `await response.json()` with no byte-level cap. A hostile or malfunctioning image generation endpoint (or an intermediary) can return an oversized JSON body that exhausts process memory during JSON parsing.\n\nThis is the same bounded-read pattern Alix-007 applied to 15+ other providers (`readProviderJsonResponse`, 16 MiB cap). Image generation was one of the remaining unbounded `.json()` call sites.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `src/image-generation/openai-compatible-image-provider.ts:272` — replace `parseOpenAiCompatibleImageResponse(await response.json(), ...)` with `readProviderJsonResponse` + `parseOpenAiCompatibleImageResponse(parsedBody, ...)`. Adds `readProviderJsonResponse` to the existing SDK import.\n- `src/image-generation/openai-compatible-image-provider.test.ts` — add `readProviderJsonResponse` to the `openclaw/plugin-sdk/provider-http` mock definition so the new import resolves in tests.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed**: unbounded `response.json()` on image generation HTTP responses; after the fix reads are capped at 16 MiB.\n- **Real environment tested**: a real `node:http` server bound to `127.0.0.1` returning a JSON body exceeding 16 MiB (20 MiB), plus a 1 MiB negative-control body, plus a valid OpenAI-compatible image response. Drives the production `readProviderJsonResponse` and `parseOpenAiCompatibleImageResponse` over a real TCP socket. Node v22.22.0.\n- **Exact steps**: `node --import tsx _proof_image_gen_json.mts` (proof script kept local-only, not committed).\n- **Evidence after fix**:\n  ```\n  === image-generation JSON response bounded read (cap=16777216) ===\n\n  PASS  Image generation JSON bounded: overflow; bytesSent=20971709; server.aborted=true\n  PASS  Image generation JSON negative control: small body parsed; cap did not trigger\n  PASS  Image generation JSON happy path: OpenAI-compatible response parsed (images created)\n\n  === All image-generation JSON bounded-read assertions passed ===\n  ```\n- **Observed result after fix**: `readProviderJsonResponse` threw the canonical overflow error when JSON body exceeded 16 MiB. Server-side `socket.bytesWritten` confirmed ~20 MiB was sent before cancellation.\n- **What was not tested**: live image generation API call (the proof exercises the same production SDK helper against the same shape of attack); cross-platform Node differences.\n\n## Out of scope\n\n- `extensions/googlechat/src/` — covered by separate PR (#3e, #96772).\n- `src/video-generation/dashscope-compatible.ts` — has 2 more unbounded `response.json()` calls; could be a follow-up if needed.\n\n## Risk\n\n- **Very low**: swap from `response.json()` to `readProviderJsonResponse`. Error behavior preserves the same upstream catch path — the helper throws `${label}: malformed JSON response` on parse errors, which is equivalent to the old JSON syntax error.\n- **Byte cap (16 MiB, default)**: invisible to normal-sized image responses (typically < 1 MiB). Only oversized/bodies trigger the new boundary.\n- **Existing SDK helper**: `readProviderJsonResponse` has been in `openclaw/plugin-sdk/provider-http` since the Alix-007 bounded-read sweep, used by 15+ providers.\n\n## Diff stats\n\n```\n2 files changed, 11 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)\n```\n\nNet code change (excl. import line + mock): **1 line** (the actual call site swap).\n",
